<section id="performance" class="doc-section">
  <h1 class="page-title">Performance</h1>

  <h2>Resource Constraints</h2>
  <p>The challenge allows a total of 1.5 CPU and 550MB RAM across all containers.</p>

  <h2>Actual Usage</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Metric</th>
        <th>Limit</th>
        <th>Actual</th>
        <th>Margin</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>RAM</td>
        <td>550MB</td>
        <td>~300MB</td>
        <td>45% below limit</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Response time</td>
        <td>—</td>
        <td>&lt; 50ms P95</td>
        <td>All requests</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Consistent latency under concurrent load</li>
    <li>Gunicorn multi-worker model handles concurrent requests effectively</li>
    <li>psycopg2 connection pooling minimizes database overhead</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL stored procedures keep business logic close to data</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Stress Testing</h2>
  <p>Load tests are run using the shared <a href="https://github.com/jonathanperis/rinha2-back-end-k6" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">rinha2-back-end-k6</a> test suite, which simulates concurrent users performing debits, credits, validations, and statement queries.</p>
